## Lesson 1.2: Overview of AI Tools & Platforms

### Major AI Assistants Comparison

#### ChatGPT (by OpenAI)
- **Best for:** General-purpose tasks, coding, creative writing
- **Strengths:** Large user community, extensive plugins, GPT-4 is highly capable
- **Free tier:** Yes (GPT-3.5)
- **Paid tier:** $20/month (GPT-4, faster responses, plugins)
- **Context window:** Up to 128K tokens (GPT-4 Turbo)

#### Claude (by Anthropic)
- **Best for:** Long documents, detailed analysis, ethical reasoning
- **Strengths:** Longer context window, excellent for summarization, safety-focused
- **Free tier:** Yes (limited)
- **Paid tier:** $20/month (Claude Pro)
- **Context window:** Up to 200K tokens (Claude 3)

#### Google Gemini
- **Best for:** Research, real-time information, Google Workspace integration
- **Strengths:** Internet access, multimodal capabilities, free access to powerful models
- **Free tier:** Yes (Gemini Pro)
- **Paid tier:** $20/month (Gemini Advanced)
- **Context window:** Up to 1M tokens (Gemini 1.5)

#### Microsoft Copilot
- **Best for:** Windows users, Office integration, web search
- **Strengths:** Built into Windows 11, free web search, Office 365 integration
- **Free tier:** Yes
- **Paid tier:** Varies by integration (e.g., Microsoft 365 Copilot)

### Specialized AI Tools

**Writing & Content:**
- **Jasper.ai**: Marketing copy and long-form content
- **Copy.ai**: Quick copywriting and ad copy
- **Grammarly**: Writing enhancement and grammar

**Design & Visual:**
- **Midjourney**: High-quality image generation
